<section class="guidelines animate-fade" style="animation-delay: 0.1s;">
  <div class="glass-card">
    <h2 class="text-gradient">Official Guidelines & Recommendations</h2>

    <div class="guideline-content">
      <div class="source-block">
        <h3>üá∫üá∏ USA Dietary Guidelines (2020-2025)</h3>
        <p>The USDA recommends a dietary pattern consisting of:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Vegetables:</strong> Approx. 400-500g (or 2.5 cup-equivalents) daily.</li>
          <li><strong>Fruits:</strong> Approx. 300-400g (or 2 cup-equivalents) daily.</li>
          <li><strong>Grains:</strong> Approx. 170g (6 ounce-equivalents) daily.</li>
          <li><strong>Dairy:</strong> Approx. 750ml or 750g (3 cup-equivalents).</li>
          <li><strong>Saturated Fat:</strong> Less than 10% of total daily calories.</li>
          <li><strong>Sodium:</strong> Less than 2,300mg per day.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="source-block">
        <h3>üá¨üáß British NHS / PHE Guidelines</h3>
        <p>The "Eatwell Guide" emphasizes:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>5 A Day:</strong> At least 5 portions of a variety of fruit and vegetables every day.</li>
          <li><strong>Hydration:</strong> 1.5 - 2 Liters (6 to 8 glasses) daily.</li>
          <li><strong>Fish:</strong> 2 portions of fish a week, one of which should be oily (like salmon).</li>
          <li><strong>Veggies:</strong> British guidelines often suggest that potatoes don't count towards your 5-a-day!</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="portions-guide">
      <h3 class="text-gradient" style="margin-bottom: 2rem; margin-top: 3rem;">What is a Portion? (Cheat Sheet)</h3>
      <div class="auto-grid portions-grid">
        <div class="portion-item">
          <span class="emoji" role="img" aria-label="Fresh Fruit and Vegetables">üçé</span>
          <div class="text">
            <strong>Fresh Fruit & Veg (80g)</strong>
            <span>1 medium apple/banana, 2 kiwis/plums, or 3 heaped tbsp of cooked veggies.</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="portion-item">
          <span class="emoji" role="img" aria-label="Dried Fruit">üçá</span>
          <div class="text">
            <strong>Dried Fruit (30g)</strong>
            <span>1 heaped tablespoon of raisins or dried apricots. Count as max 1 portion/day.</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="portion-item">
          <span class="emoji" role="img" aria-label="Juice and Smoothies">ü•§</span>
          <div class="text">
            <strong>Juice / Smoothies</strong>
            <span>Limit to 150ml per day. Sugars are released impacting teeth and blood sugar.</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="portion-item">
          <span class="emoji" role="img" aria-label="Meat and Fish">ü•©</span>
          <div class="text">
            <strong>Meat / Fish</strong>
            <span>Size of a deck of cards or palm of your hand (approx 90g cooked).</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="portion-item">
          <span class="emoji" role="img" aria-label="Cheese">üßÄ</span>
          <div class="text">
            <strong>Cheese</strong>
            <span>Size of a matchbox (approx 30g). High in calcium but also saturated fat.</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="portion-item">
          <span class="emoji" role="img" aria-label="Carbs">üçö</span>
          <div class="text">
            <strong>Carbs (Pasta/Rice)</strong>
            <span>Size of your clenched fist (cooked) or a tennis ball.</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

